 psychiatry. Doctors have thus imposed white or black racial identities upon every organ system of the human body, along with racial interpretations of black children, the black elderly, the black athlete, black musicality, black pain thresholds, and other aspects of black minds and bodies. The American medical establishment does not readily absorb either historical or current information about medical racism. For this reason, racial enlightenment will not reach medical schools until the current race-aversive curricula include new historical and sociological perspectives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAfrican AmericansxMedical carezUnited States. 0aDiscrimination in medical carezUnited States. 0aHealth services accessibilityzUnited States. 0aMinoritiesxMedical carezUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aaccess to healthcare.  aafrican americans and healthcare.  aamerican doctors.  aamerican health care.  aamerican healthcare.  abioethics.  abooks for healthcare professionals.  abooks for med students.  abooks for pa students.  abooks for physicians.  adiagnosis and treatment.  adiscrimination and racism.  ahealth and race.  ahealthcare and racism.  amedical code of ethics.  amedical discrimination.  amedical ethics.  amedical humanities.  amedical racism.  amedicine and racism.  arace in america.  aracial stereotypes.  asociology and medicine.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024890840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095184640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520951846423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520951846/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000